# Samsara project rules

## Phase gate
- Check `docs/business/SCOPE.md` **Status** before implementing features.
- If status is `DRAFT` or not `APPROVED`: only edit docs, structure, or scope — no backend/frontend feature code.
- After scope is `APPROVED`: write `docs/product/USER_JOURNEY.md` and `USE_CASES.md` before scaffolding apps.

## Layout
- Planning lives in `docs/` — see `docs/README.md`.
- New application code goes in `backend/` (FastAPI) or `frontend/` — never in `legacy/`.
- Legacy under `legacy/` is read-only reference; port logic instead of extending.

## Stack (when building)
- API: FastAPI + MongoDB (v1+). MVP is local-first per business scope.
- Product name in UI: **Samsara** (not Mindful Journey).

## Efficiency
- Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/README.md` first; avoid duplicating scope across files.
- Prefer small, module-scoped changes aligned with docs/product use case IDs (once written).

## Safety
- No substance sourcing, no medical prescriptions, no replacing 911/sitter/therapist.
- User-facing flows need harm-reduction disclaimers per `docs/business/SCOPE.md` §8.
